Package org.ivoa.dm.dataset.dataset

Class DataID

java.lang.Object
org.ivoa.dm.dataset.dataset.DataID
All Implemented Interfaces:
org.ivoa.vodml.jpa.JPAManipulations, org.ivoa.vodml.jpa.JPAManipulationsForObjectType<Long>
@Entity @VoDml(id="ds:dataset.DataID", role=objectType) public class DataID extends Object implements org.ivoa.vodml.jpa.JPAManipulationsForObjectType<Long>
The Data Identification object (DataID) stores the dataset identifiers and other metadata typically assigned by the dataset creator. The Dataset IDs in this object must comply with the syntax for dataset identifiers defined in the 'IVOA Identifiers' document, including the use of 'stop' characters to identify specific datasets that are not individually in the registry. e.g., ivo://example.net/aservice?2013/5/2342. Much of the content of this object is assembled from various definitions in the IVAO Resource Metadata document. Here, we provide a brief description of each field for easy reference, along with a notation of its mapping to the Resource Metadata document (RM:field), where the reader may find more detailed information. objectType: DataID

    • _id

    • title

      @VoDml(id="ds:dataset.DataID.title", role=attribute, type="ivoa:string", typeRole=primitiveType) protected String title
      A free form string giving a title for the dataset. (RM:Identity.Title). : Attribute title : multiplicity 1

    • datasetID

      @VoDml(id="ds:dataset.DataID.datasetID", role=attribute, type="ivoa:anyURI", typeRole=primitiveType) protected String datasetID
      If the dataset is registered with an external 'global index service' such as ADS, the publisher may include that identifier here. This provides a common, persistent identifier for the dataset, and possible access point to follow for information on publications and other related datasets. Note: the same dataset published at more than one location would have different Curation.publisherDID values, but the same DataID.datasetID. eg: 'ivo://ADS/Sa.CXO?obsid=1234', 'ivo://ADS/sh.hut#ngc4151_141' . : Attribute datasetID : multiplicity 0..1

    • creatorDID

      @VoDml(id="ds:dataset.DataID.creatorDID", role=attribute, type="ivoa:anyURI", typeRole=primitiveType) protected String creatorDID
      The dataset identifier assigned by the creator. Here, the authority-id of the identifier must be that of the creator. It is used to identify the original exposure of the dataset in an archive, and will remain static regardless of where the dataset is published. The creator ID will not necessarily change even if the VO object in question is a cutout or is otherwise further processed. : Attribute creatorDID : multiplicity 0..1

    • version

      @VoDml(id="ds:dataset.DataID.version", role=attribute, type="ivoa:string", typeRole=primitiveType) protected String version
      Version assigned by the creator, reflecting the production version of the dataset. This value should only be changed by the creator, upon the new release of a dataset. There are no format restrictions or specifications on the versioning scheme. : Attribute version : multiplicity 0..1

    • date

      @VoDml(id="ds:dataset.DataID.date", role=attribute, type="ivoa:datetime", typeRole=primitiveType) protected Date date
      Data processing or creation date (RM:Curation.Date). : Attribute date : multiplicity 0..1

    • creationType

      @VoDml(id="ds:dataset.DataID.creationType", role=attribute, type="ds:dataset.CreationType", typeRole=enumeration) protected CreationType creationType
      The dataset creation type describes the nature or genre of the content. (RM:General.Type). Note: This field provides information about the process by which the dataset was created. As the Observation/Experiment model matures, this may evolve into a provenance element on the Experiment type. : Attribute creationType : multiplicity 0..1

    • creator

      @VoDml(id="ds:dataset.DataID.creator", role=composition, type="ds:dataset.Creator", typeRole=objectType) protected Creator creator
      The institution or entity which created the dataset. composition creator : ( Multiplicity : 0..1 )

    • contributor

      @VoDml(id="ds:dataset.DataID.contributor", role=composition, type="ds:dataset.Contributor", typeRole=objectType) protected List<Contributor> contributor
      Persons or entities who contributed to the generation of the scientific content of the dataset. Users of the dataset should include these in subsequent credits and acknowledgements. (RM:Curation.Contributor). composition contributor : ( Multiplicity : 0..* )

    • collection

      @VoDml(id="ds:dataset.DataID.collection", role=composition, type="ds:dataset.Collection", typeRole=objectType) protected List<Collection> collection
      The dataset is associated with zero or more Collections (instrument name, survey name, etc.) . Each instance identifies a tag indicating some degree of compatibility with other data sharing the same Collection properties. composition collection : ( Multiplicity : 0..* )
